    94→
    95→    /**
    96→     * Returns a value of type T equal to the elements of the list applied in sequence to one another
    97→     * with the given operator. This happens from right-to-left (i.e., from tail() to head()). The
    98→     * zero value is used to the right of the list's last non-empty value. If the list is empty, the
